Exhibit A. California Privacy Addendum
1. What is this statement for?
This privacy statement explains the reasons we process your personal data, how we collect and handle your data, how we ensure its protection, how it is used, and the rights you have concerning your personal data. This statement applies to all individuals applying for roles with us and describes how we process your personal information as part of the recruitment process for our
Affiliates
.
In addition, California residents can consult
Exhibit A
which outlines additional rights and provisions.
We act as the “data controller” with respect to the information described in this Statement, and our contact information is provided at the end of this Statement.
2. To whom is this statement applicable?
This statement applies to job applicants, including those who submit CVs, cover letters, and other relevant personal data as part of the recruitment process, whether for a current position or in response to an open call. It also extends to candidates who are directly contacted by the Company for potential opportunities. For information about how we process personal information outside of such relationships, please see our
Website Privacy Policy
.
For purposes of the CCPA, this Statement supplements the
Website Privacy Policy
.
3. What personal data are we processing, for what purpose, legal basis, and period?
As part of the recruitment process, we will process various types of personal data. The legal basis mentioned in the below table is alternative and can vary based on the jurisdiction where we operate, considering the particularities of the local legislation.
For California residents, we have identified the categories of Personal Information collected in
Exhibit A
attached at the end of this Statement.
Purpose
Legal Basis
Categories of Data
Retention Period
Recruitment Process
Performance of a contract, legitimate interest
Name, contact information, CV, cover letter, job preferences, qualifications, professional background
For non-advancing candidates: during the recruitment process and after the end of the process in accordance with applicable laws.
Background Checks
Consent, legal obligations, legitimate interest
Employment history, references, criminal record checks (if applicable) or data you made publicly accessible (e.g. your LinkedIn profile)
For non-advancing candidates: during the recruitment process and for a period not exceeding the maximum statutory period required by law.
Interview Process
Performance of a contract, legitimate interest
Interview feedback, test results, communications during the interview
For non-advancing candidates: during the recruitment process and for a period not exceeding the maximum statutory period required by law.
Legal and Regulatory Compliance
Legal obligation
Identification details, nationality, work eligibility documents (e.g., visa, work permits)
For non-advancing candidates: during the recruitment process and for a period not exceeding the maximum statutory period required by law.
Diversity and Equal Opportunities
Consent or legitimate interest
Gender, nationality, ethnicity (optional for diversity purposes)
For non-advancing candidates: during the recruitment process and for a period not exceeding the maximum statutory period required by law.
Internal Analytical Purposes
Legitimate interest
Anonymized data regarding applications, selection process outcomes, and demographic information
Anonymized data can be kept indefinitely for internal statistical purposes.
The personal data will be used only for the recruitment process and for determining your suitability for a role. We may also use your data for internal administrative purposes related to the recruitment process.
4. Where are we obtaining your personal data from?
We primarily collect your personal data directly from you through your application, CV, and other documents provided during the recruitment process. In some cases, we may collect personal data from:
Referees
: Information such as your previous employment details and performance, if applicable.
Public Sources
: For example, LinkedIn or other professional networks, where we may collect your public profile details, including work history, qualifications, and skills.
Third Parties
: We may also collect information from third parties, including your former employers, credit reference agencies, background check providers, or publicly available resources (such as social media networks).
If you fail to provide personal data when requested, which is necessary for us to consider your application (such as evidence of qualifications or work history), or to enter a contract with you, we may not be able to process your application further.
5. How will we use your data?
We will use the personal data collected about you to:
Assess your skills, qualifications, and suitability for the role.
Carry out background checks, reference checks, or criminal record checks where applicable and in accordance with the law.
Communicate with you about your application and the recruitment process.
Comply with legal, regulatory, or contractual obligations.
For internal analytical purposes: We may aggregate and anonymize your personal data to analyze recruitment trends, improve the efficiency of our recruitment process, and monitor diversity and inclusion efforts. The anonymized data will be used for internal analysis, and no personally identifiable information will be retained in this context.
6. Will we use your sensitive data?
We may collect and process sensitive data such as:
Disability status
: For the purpose of providing reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process (e.g., special accommodations for interviews or tests).
Nationality or ethnicity
: For compliance with immigration laws or for diversity purposes.
We will only use this data where permitted by law and with your consent where required, if permitted by the applicable legislation.
7. Automated decision-making
You will not be subject to decisions based solely on automated processing that would have a legal or similarly significant effect on you during the recruitment process.
8. Data sharing
Your personal data may be shared with third parties, including:
Our recruitment team and hiring managers
: To assess your suitability for the role.
Background check providers
: For reference checks or verification of qualifications.
External service providers
: For technical support in managing the recruitment process (e.g., recruitment platforms or applicant tracking systems).
Legal authorities or other public bodies
: As required by law, such as verifying work permits or immigration status.
All third-party service providers are, where required by law, bound by confidentiality agreements and data protection agreements and are required to process your personal data in line with our data protection policies.
The personal data you entrust to our company may be transferred outside the country of your residence, including third countries. Where required by law, any transfer will be made subject to an adequate contract laying down the conditions of the transfer in accordance with the applicable privacy laws or in accordance with legal provisions.
Your personal information will be transferred to the United States of America to Manychat, Inc.
9. Data security
We have implemented appropriate security measures to protect your personal data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include technical and organizational safeguards, such as encryption and restricted access. If you suspect any breach of your data security, please contact us immediately.
10. Data retention
Your data will be deleted after the end of the recruitment process, in accordance with applicable laws, if you are not selected for the role. If you are selected for a role, we will retain your data for the duration of your employment and subsequently for any statutory period required by law. If we will not advance with your application, we may retain your data, with your consent, for up to 1 year to potentially consider you for future openings, unless you request otherwise.
After the expiration of these retention periods, your personal data will be securely deleted or anonymized for internal analysis in accordance with applicable law. The anonymized data may be retained indefinitely for purposes such as recruitment process improvement or monitoring diversity and inclusion, but it will no longer be identifiable to you.
For California residents, we are required by law to maintain records of requests submitted under the California Consumer Privacy Act and how we responded to such requests for at least 24 months. We only use this information for recordkeeping purposes.
11. Your data subject rights
California residents have additional rights set out in
Exhibit A
below. Under applicable data protection laws, you have several rights regarding your personal data depending on your jurisdiction or the jurisdiction in which you are applying, including the right to:
Right to Access and Information: You have the right to request access to your personal data held by the employer, as well as information about how your data is processed and any relevant aspects of this processing, including types of data, purposes of processing and third parties to whom the data is shared.
Right to confirmation of the existence of the processing.
Right to Rectification: You have the right to request the correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal data held by the employer.
Right to Erasure: You have the right to request the deletion of your personal data, subject to certain legal and contractual limitations, including the necessity to comply with applicable employment and legal obligations.
Right to Restriction of Processing: You have the right to request a restriction on the processing of your personal data under certain circumstances, such as if the data is inaccurate or the processing is unlawful.
Right to Data Portability: You have the right to receive your personal data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format and, where feasible, to transmit that data to another controller.
Right to Object: You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data, particularly where the processing is based on legitimate interests, direct marketing, or profiling.
Right Not to Be Subject to Automated Decision-Making: You have the right not to be subject to decisions based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which have legal or similarly significant effects.
Right to refuse the consent for the processing of your personal data or to revoke such given consent.
Right to lodge a complaint to the competent national supervisory authority.
To exercise these rights, please contact us at
privacy@manychat.com
. We will handle your request in line with applicable data protection laws and aim to respond within a reasonable timeframe and in accordance with the limits set by the law.
12. Contact for data protection inquiries
If you have any questions about this statement or how we process your personal data, please contact us at
privacy@manychat.com
.
